<topic id='supporting_definition_nhs_continuing_healthcare_local_appeal.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Supporting Information: NHS Continuing Healthcare Local Appeal - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_nhs_continuing_healthcare_local_appeal">NHS Continuing Healthcare Local Appeal</xref>
 is an individual request for a review of an 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_continuing_healthcare">NHS Continuing Healthcare</xref>
 eligibility decision, by the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 or their 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_patient_proxy">Patient Proxy</xref>
 to the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_clinical_commissioning_group">Clinical Commissioning Group</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_clinical_commissioning_group">CCG</xref>), following a full assessment undertaken using the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_decision_support_tool_for_nhs_continuing_healthcare">Decision Support Tool for NHS Continuing Healthcare</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_nhs_continuing_healthcare_local_appeal">NHS Continuing Healthcare Local Appeals</xref>
 are those that are addressed through the local 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_nhs_continuing_healthcare_local_resolution">NHS Continuing Healthcare Local Resolution</xref>
 process by the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_clinical_commissioning_group">Clinical Commissioning Group</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_clinical_commissioning_group">CCG</xref>) and do not include Independent Reviews or Ombudsman complaints.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_nhs_continuing_healthcare_local_appeal">Local Appeal</xref>
 is complete at the point the outcome of the 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_nhs_continuing_healthcare_local_resolution">NHS Continuing Healthcare Local Resolution</xref>
 process is communicated to the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 or their 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_patient_proxy">Patient Proxy</xref>
 (i.e. the date a decision letter is sent), or the request is discounted (for those requests that are withdrawn or not appropriate).        </p>
  </div>
